==English==

===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|striven|striven||lang=enm}} "to strive" from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|estriver|estriver||lang=fro}} "to compete, quarrel" from {{fro}} {{term|estrif|estrif||lang=fro}} "quarrel, dispute", alteration (influenced by {{etyl|gem}} forms related to {{etyl|frk}} *{{term||strīban||lang=frk}} "to strive", compare {{etyl|dum|-}} {{term|streven|streven||lang=dum}} "to strive", {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|streben|streben||lang=de}} "to strive") of {{fro}} {{term|estrit|estrit||lang=fro}}, of {{etyl|gem}} origin, from {{etyl|frk}} *{{term||strīd||lang=frk}} "quarrel, dispute" from {{proto|gem-pro|strīdō|combat, strife|lang=en}}. Akin to {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|strit|strīt||lang=goh}} "quarrel" ({{de}} {{term|Streit|Streit||lang=de}}), {{goh}} {{term|stritan|strītan||lang=goh}} "to fight", {{etyl|non|-}} {{term|strið|strīð||lang=non}} "strife, contention". More at [[stride]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈstɻaɪv/}}
* {{audio|En-us-strive.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|aɪv}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|strives|striving|'''[[strove]]''' or '''[[strived]]'''|'''[[striven]]''' or '''[[strived]]'''}}

# To [[try]] to [[achieve]] a [[result]]; to make [[strenuous]] effort; to try earnestly and persistently.
#: ''He strove to excel.''
# To [[struggle]] in opposition; to be in contention or dispute; to [[contend]]; to [[contest]].
#: ''to strive against fate''
#: ''to strive for the truth''

====Usage notes====
* This is a [[catenative]] verb that takes the ''to infinitive''. See [[Appendix:English catenative verbs]]
* The [[strong]] or [[irregular]] forms "[[strove]]" and "[[striven]]" are more commonly used in print than "[[strived]]".

